name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
Nice park to catch the sunrise. Peaceful and serene.  There are folks having group exercises at the amphitheatre area and people fishing early in the morning.

The only downside is the very limited number of parking lots.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: This park is perfect for a peaceful evening walk, with its serene water and lush greenery helping to calm your mind - one of its biggest selling points. While we were there, the boating rides, primarily kayaking, were unavailable, and the children's play area was being renovated. However, the park is well-connected and close to both the bus stop and Khatib MRT station, which are within walking distance. I look forward to visiting this park again in the future.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Very vibrant place for a small weekend meetup with friends(not more than 5). Cycling groups were also spotted passing by this area. Limited parking lots, I was lucky to get a lot when I reached slightly after 8pm. Enjoy the view!

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
A very beautiful park with quite huge water body.

I’m surprised that this park has no shops attached to it but that’s ok. It’s good to have a walk or jog here but for those thinking of skating or something, please don’t as the floors are not smooth.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: A nice place to relax and catch the sunrise. There will be elderly group doing their morning training regularly. Would be better if there is a bigger parking or easier access to the opposite carpark.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
For three yrs staying in Singpore this is my first time to visit here ❤
The weather is hot and it is not crowded. I observe Me and you can stay here and do the picnic especially to my co- OFW workers ! If I visit again this place I like to try riding the boat. The time is so limited for me that day, cause I do have some appointment too attend. This place is very beautiful I hope i can visit again and stay longer to experience the spot of this tourist spot.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice reservoir park that provides rental of kayak, managed by Camelot. We rented a double kayak with my 9-yr-old boy for two hours. It was a thoroughly enjoyable experience. Footwear is compulsory (minimally slippers). Lockers are available and free to use. Downside, no shower facilities at the public toilet and parking spaces are rather limited.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
A nice park for a quick evening stroll. Wherever there is water and greenery, that just helps your mind to relax which is the biggest plus point for any park.

I believe they do have boating rides available mainly kayaking but it was closed when we visited. Even the children play area was under construction.

Very well connected and is just near to the bus stop as well as Khatib MRT (walking distance). I would definitely love to visit here often.

PS: I heard sunset pics do come out fabulous here. Must try next time 😃

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
Khatib mrt 🚶‍♂️ walk less than 20minutes towards Traffic junction, Reservoirs on the Left.

Or

Prefer An hour brisk walking  🚶‍♂️ 🚶‍♀️ from SpringLeaf MRT 5mins to Springleaf natures park  Entrance Turn Right  ... walk along the Canal  Straight ahead until the end And walk staircase up to main road on the *Right able to see Lower Seletar Reservoirs.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Good place to go for a stroll in the morning. Good for kayaking as the water is calm and clear. Spotted sting rays and fishes.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Gorgeous place for meditation, stretching, nature walks and some peace n quiet. Only 1 public toilet available however. And some vending machines for drinks/snacks... payable by phone.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Enjoyed coming here all the time. I live nearby and it is always a comfort place to come to. However due to the rain the bridge are starting to grow algae... Quite a sad thing to see. Hope there could be some maintenance to be done. It is a rather crowded location for wkends. They also have 2 rented gardening area for people who would like to have their own space for gardening. These are some photos of the gardening area

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice place. Different view from macritchie. Good place to jog and run. Keep it clean and beautiful Folks!

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Breathtaking sunrise view. Have a walk after catching sunrise~ with perfect lake reflection.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Lovely water front park with jetties and a  water play area. It's not particularly big but it still makes for a pleasant walk and it also connects to the Springleaf Park Connector seamlessly.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
Good sunset view. Breezy at night.
Water fountain for children to run ard. Good facilities benches, toilet.
No stinky smell

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
We had a nice picnic at the Lower Seletar Reservoir Park to celebrate a special occasion. There are a few pavilions in the park that you can reserve for a picnic.

Even with rainy and cloudy weather, it was a nice experience to be out in nature and enjoy the sunset and evening. Make sure to bring your insect repellent especially if you are planning to come around dawn or dusk.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice place to visit to admire the evening scene at the reservoir. A place for fishing, canoeing or kayaking. Also a small fruit farm to admire its produces. Also noticed that the pink snail eggs have invaded the reservoir as well.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice place to have leisure morning/evening walk..we also did dragon boat race here

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice place to hangout but less no of parking. Kids play with waters.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: really nice and scenic reservoir that is pretty accessible (~12 min walk from khatib mrt). love the design of some of their phototaking spots. blessed with good weather hence nice reflection of sky and clouds 😍

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Beautiful place. Too bad the car park area are too small. Only about 10 vehicles can park there. Serene & calming place. Love it

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Beautiful, windy place to ride and chill. Just take note that no bbq allowed in this park and certain areas require u to push your bicycle around.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Another great park.  Walked from Rower's bay park & connected to Lower seletar reservoir park about 4km away.  Love the fact that all the parks are so easily accessible & great walking path & trails too.  If one is tired , the bus stop is just a stone throw away.  Made the discovery that one can walk to Springleaf Nature park thru the PCN connector.  It says 20mins away but as I start walking it became 40mins... Endeed up taking a bus before Sg seletar bridge as by then was feeling tired after having walked 15km... All in all, I thought that was pretty good a hike

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
A rare place in Singapore where you can see sun rise and sunset at a water horizon at same location with about 12hours apart.

Sun rise at about 6.45am and sunset starts at around 6.15pm. Vary by the months and weather.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Small public free parking area. But otherwise beautiful reservoir for a stroll in the evening when it's not so hot

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Perfect place to chill and enjoy the view of sunset. Public toilet and fitness corner at your convenience.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: A beautiful and tranquil park. Rejuvenate or meditate. It is up to you.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice place, need more drinking fountains and shelter.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: It was drizzling when I went a few weeks ago, i didn't take much pictures but the scenery was still beautiful, will go again some days.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
A nice cosy area to relax and breathe fresh air.
Passed by hundreds and thousand times but didn't visit at all.  Today just want to run away from home awhile.  Decided to come and explore.  I love it, not very crowded and good for my gal to ride her bicycle a little.
Water area around here too for kids.
Peaceful for mind and a
Beautiful place.
A public toilet 🚻available and for people who loves canoeing, you can find it here.

Keep the park as cosy as it is.
Free carpark with limited slots though...
Will be back soon.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: A beautiful reservoir to relax and do nothing... could see some people gather together for a picnic, and chatting and laughing...

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
For pure serenity and scenery, this is the place for tortured souls.  Even though it is right besides two of the busiest vehicular traffic routes and a venerable MRT overhead track, it faces a wide waterway devoid of buildings and planes.

Forget driving there due to very limited parking lots. It's best to either cycle or walk there.

No shops. No bicycle rental sheds. No noisy kids, too. Lots of anglers. Lots of sunshine.  Lots of flotsam too.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Very serene place in the morning and come with great sunrise view!

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice park for briskwalk and scenery w/waters background.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Wanted to walk to the dam for sunrise but the heritage bridge seemed interesting. Landed upon a treasure of a place, so serene, peaceful and relaxing with locals jogging biking, meditating, practicing Tai Chi, yoga or just there for sunrise photography. The amphitheater before the bridge is filled with active people and activities as well. Walking along the park is very pleasant especially due to tree cover. There is kayak rental as well as place for fishing.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: A small park with some small water play and a small free car park. The wooden deck at the jetty looks run-down

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
Nice place to chill....over a beer or some chilled drinks. You can see people having picnic at this place, cycling and jogging.

There are some simple water fountain for kids to get drench and simply be kids- having fun.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Can fish legally here though there is limited fish available and they are usually quite far from the shore. Picnic under the shade of the mrt tracks and watch the cyclists and joggers. Good place to relax and excellent location to watch the sunset 🌆. Kayaking and dragon boat races are available too.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Wonderful place. Peaceful with serenity. This place a great for sunrise but the sunset is also nice. There's exercise corner n water play ground. A small free public carpark is available. A bridge with lights and a small jetty for sampans makes great photography opportunities.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
Nice small park along the reservior, clear water
It's more of a residental park along Yishun Ave 1.
Trees and benches along the park and could find squirrels running around.
Cool, breezy which is good for excercise, evening walk for elders and jogging.
A playground and water play area for kids too.
A heritage bridge which design/build to look like "kelong" on stilts where one could relax, enjoy the view and cool air. Along the bridge you could find  information regarding the histroy of the area.
A large deck for fishing enthusiastic and Kayaking is also available at an affordable price.
Good view for sunrise/sunset and view of MRT passing through.
You could also see otter swimming / diving in the clear water.
Nice view of birds flying low above the water after sun set.
Tortoise could also be seen swimming along.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
Nice windy weather. Great place to fish.
But too much fresh water weed. Lures
Always get entangled by the weeds.
Only surfaced lures with wire disentangles it. Still can carry on fishzzing🐟🐟🐟

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Lovely place with myraclous view.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
Lovely & tranquility. You can come earlier in the morning, watch the amazing sunrise, run,walk, kayaking in the reservoir. I can walk to Springleaf Nature Park or walk to Yishun Dam. You can watch beautiful sunset here too.If you like to continue walking, can continue walking to Punggol Marina. But it is rather quiet from this stretch though. Of course, cycling is another option for leisure.
You can walk to Seletar Airpirt from Yishun Dam too. It is pretty amazing that you can discover around this area. I just love this place.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
Calm and almost quiet place to spend an evening with family. Well maintained and is a sunset location. There is a small water play area for the kids. My son enjoyed playing there though the water was only up to his knee.

There were people fishing at one end and it seems to be a good location for fishing as well. Planning to visit again.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: It's not crowded, not for tourists but for the residents. You get a good view of the lake and the sunset. Have made a mission to see the 🌄 one of these days. The wind was breezy and cool. Nice place to just sit down and relax. Good place to meditate with all the natural elements surrounding you. Some went there to fish.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
A really peaceful park. You can go there and kayak as well.
To get there by MRT & BUS:
• Take MRT to Khatib, opposite the Khatib station take the bus 969 (stop at the second station (after Yishun Sports Stadium)

I went there today, however it was raining heavily and had to seek shelter, waited around an hour and I could finally take a walk in the park.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
Always travel by mrt and only look from above in seconds.
5 days ago, take a cool walk, its rain heavily and stop. Enjoy the breeze, saw the old bridge for fishing and also the new extension that goes further into the reservoir. Like the water play for kids.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Beautiful, clean water, and nice connector to walk/run or even bring your toddler! This place have 'mini' water park where you can take off your footwear and walk inside shallow water. ;) my toddler and I definitely enjoyed our time and walk around this area!

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: A beautiful gem in the north located along Yishun ave 1. Due to its remote location, this is not a busy park. Perfect for jogging and evening stroll with beautiful scenery. There’s no playground around but the water play features is good enough to keep kids occupied provided if they intend to get wet. For adults, just relax, literally do nothing and clear your mind.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Had been meaning to visit this reservoir for quite sometime and finally got the time to do so. I planned and reached during Sunset and the views were amazing. The park itself is not that big as such won’t take much time to explore. However, it is well maintained and fishing is allowed so you will find a number of people trying their luck in it.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice place for morning/evening walks

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Beautiful place suitable for 3 generation. A place for relaxing and refueling away from the stress of the city. The water play area, the heritage bridge, the pathway for you to enjoy the view of the reservoir, lower seletar reservoir park is a perfect place for family's leisure activities.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice park.  Well maintain.  Good plc to exercise.  Surrounded by greenery.  Calm water to see reflexion.  Heritage bridge is  well design & built.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Very nice and relaxing to be in this place! Big area to jog and ride your bike, for kids, there is a water fountain and playground. It is along yishun ave 1.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Very scenic and serene reservoir park. Good place for bird watching, especially during the harvesting of water weeds where the grey herons and other birds come to feast on organism trapped in the weeds. A little problematic for parking if driving there, may need to park at the HDB estate and walk over.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Beautiful views of Lower Seletar Reservoir and Orchid Country Club. Breathing in fresh air and breezy greenery. Safe heaven to bring children to appreciate nature. Fishing jogging exercise meditation or just relax and rejuvenate. Clean tidy friendly cosy comfy welcoming ambience for romantic intimates groups students tourists expats locals visitors and families. Conveniently located in the neighbourhood heartland next to Khatin MRT station connecting to Yishun MRT with Northpoint City and bus interchange with plenty of dinning shopping banking library postage community centre cinemas entertainment supermarkets and amenities nearby..

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
Tried out the designated fishing area. Started 6:30 and already people out and about walking , jogging exercising and taking pictures of the beautiful sunrise. Good facilities and also have water themed area for kids, kayaking available at the reservoir also. The car park is small and can get filled up quickly especially in the mornings and weekends, there is an HDB carpark in the area opposite.
All fishing caught on barbless hook and returned safely 👍

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
Great recreation place where you can choose to just stroll, cycle, go boating and get the kids indulge in the water play.

Also a popular spot for picnicking.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Awesome and relaxing place.  Good rest stop if you are cycling at night.  Toilet and drink fountains available here.  There looks to be some vendos too.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice views, but little parking path is remarkably short, not even able to circumnavigate the reservoir. Good for kids and kayaking and that's about it. Government should redesign the place.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Those who brisk walk can try taking this route. Go for early Indian breakfast at the casuarina restaurant which open as early as 0700. After which proceed out and follow the sign board to the upper reservoir.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Quiet and surreal park. Some people went there to fish. You can also walk to Spring leaf Nature Park to do some bird watching

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Windy and scenery place for exercise. If you think the park size is unable to fulfil your workout energy, you can always use the park connector and go to Springleaf Nature Park as well.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice place, will be nicer if there're more trees & larger playground

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
Sunny day at Lower Seletar
Reservoir Park saw ants finding food ; monitor lizard suntanning itself n also mother n her baby lovely moment at the park .

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
A small park that has a great view of the sunrise and the sunset over the water.

There are many people who come here to run, walk and cycle.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: BEAUTIFUL LONG WALK, NICE BREEZE AND LOTS OF WILD BIRDS TO SEE. HERONS, EGRETS, SWIFTS, ETC. RIGHT TURN OUT OF MRT N 10 TO 15MINS WALK TO PARK, AFTER WALKING PASS A BIG AREA FOR SEAFOOD N FISHING.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Had a lovely early morning stroll before catching a mesmerising sun rise over the mirror like waters.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice view for sunrise and sunset

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
Small carpark, but free. We parked in the HDB across the street.

The park is relatively small but it’s super calm and relaxing. Highly recommend for a walk, not a jog.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Pretty good place to enjoy the scenery, but can be a little crowded in the evening. ..

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Good place for multiple activities but too bad sometimes have people drinking & smoking there at night, hope the enforcement officer will go there more often to check on them.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Very scenic and breezy at the park. Has a fitness corner and a water park within as well as 2 fishing jetties. Carpark is way too small, maximum of 15 lots. You have to park opposite, across the road, near Yishun stadium. Can be quite crowded during the weekends.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Please prepare mosquitos /insect repellent as there are quite a lot of mosquitos during evening.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice place to relax, free your mind, jogging and walking. Plus nice views.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park

review_text:
A smaller reservoir when compared to Upper Seletar reservoir but has nice n shady areas to walk.
Nice garden plots for hire.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice to place to relax in the morning and evening, esp the jetty. This place like a rubbish dump on Saturday and Sunday mornings. Liquor bottles,  plastic bottles,  plastic bags,  wrappers, etc litter everywhere. Can the authorities be act before this place becomes a ruin?  Enforcement is needed here in the early mornings here

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Great place to kayak and walks. Really scenic. There is a small carpark, don't drive too fast because you will probably miss the carpark entrance and have to do 2 U turns to get back to the carpark entrance.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Good place to rest and stretch your leg. Also the view is great. It is a good place to fishing too.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: A serene reservoir  with water splashing play park for children's. Free parking as well but limited or may park opposite at hdb side. Bus reachable too.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Peaceful as not as popular as other parks. One downside is visitors tend to play loud music sometimes, or just loud voices. Also, this is a small park.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
The Lower Seletar Reservoir Park is a small patch of greenery along Yishun Avenue 1 until it meets Lentor Avenue. The park is facing south so sunrise is generally to the left of the reservoir.

The shape of the reservoir from the park presents sunrise in a much better angle than sunset as the sun will rise over the water. On  still mornings, spectacular sunrise can be captured on camera and it gives a dreamy cacophony of colors.

The park is full of morning and evening joggers as the thick trees provides a good shade across the day. There is a kayak rental shack if you decide to get on the water.

There is an amphitheater for shows or just to enjoy the breeze. The park has two jetties where visitors can stroll and enjoy the view.

Pictures attached are copyrighted to me.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Stunning sun rises and morning scenes. Nice place to start your day. Almost can't picture this to be in Singapore.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Kayaking available from 8.30am to 5pm daily except Monday and Thursday. Affordable $12 for 2 hours per pax. Nice view.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Tranquil park great for walkers, joggers and cyclists.  Great place to catch sunrise.  Do watch out for trains running regularly on tracks above the reservoir edge.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Beautiful and lovely place. Nice and quiet. Used to have my dragonboat training here. Toilet here are not really clean but bearable. Overall the park is very clean. Great place to chill out. Big water play area for the kids. Awesome sunrise. The only problem is limited parking spaces. Otherwise there is more parking spaces opposite hdb block.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Super chill spot

review_text: Great place for relaxing

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Had a photoshoot done for a friend and his best men a few weeks back. Very relaxing and family friendly place to be. You can see Orchid Country Club golf courses on the other side. A few activities for the young with the fountain area. Fresh air and not very crowded even on Sundays.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: My usual morning jogging route... Nice place for sunrise

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Best place to watch sunrise. Be there by 7am. Even without sunrise the view.is scenic and tranquil as it is far from the crowd, yet convenient location with jusr about 10min walk from Khatid MRT.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Feel so peaceful on Friday afternoon. Not much people here. Hot with some wind.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Love the smell of nature and the smell of salty water. Love the colour of the sky when the sun is setting.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Beautiful scenery 🥰..I love it..good for running & jogging.. site seing

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
A small park by the reservoir side, opposite the zoo, along Yishun Ave 1.
Though small, but have the facilities like public toilet, share bicycle, kayak rental, a fountain pool for kids, and even a bridge that stretches to the mid reservoir, just to catch a glimpse of the nature.
Some part of the park still under construction, and some area, are full of fire ants, and potholes too.
Really have to be alert when cycling or running or walking, otherwise, accidents can happen.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Beautiful place for relaxing with family and friends. Photos taking.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Lovely small reservoir for residents of khatib/yishun. Amazing view for sunset/sunrise.

Clean and nice park, lots of shade and seating with tables!

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: The Lower Seletar Reservoir and the Lower Seletar Reservoir Park is managed by the Public Utilities Board of Singapore and the National Parks Board respectively. The park is a pleasant place for leisure activities, both on land and in water. The park features a Family Bay with a new performance stage, a water play area, a bioswale rain garden, as well as a Heritage Bridge, allowing something for everyone. The reservoir has certain areas specifically designed for fishing hobbyist however, only artificial baits are allowed so as to prevent water pollution. Overall, it is a great location for family activities with water play park, gardens as well as facilities for exercising. Do bring along your smartphone or a camera to capture the beautiful sunrise and sunset.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park, albeit relatively small compared to other parks and reservoirs, is a definite worthy pit-stop if you're in the region. As you traverse the short path, the reservoir is always in view. Unlike smaller reservoirs and ponds, the view for Lower Seletar Reservoir Park is actually quite extensive, such that you have to strain your eyes to see the other side of the water, if you are able to see anything at all. Personally, I got a bit of Chek Jawa vibes, as the waters were really far out. Within the park itself I suggest visiting both the Heritage Bridge and Fishing Deck, though despite its name you can see people fishing all along Lower Seletar Reservoir Park. These two are protrusions of land into the water and are sure to provide a scenic view and ambience.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
实里达蓄水池（Lower Seletar Reservoir）是位于新加坡北部的义顺新镇以东的水库。该水库的表面积为3.6平方公里，容量为950万立方米，平均深度为2 m，最大深度为5.5 m。海岸线长度为14.3公里。
公园24小时开放免费入场。

喜欢钓鱼的钓友在水库那边有两个木桥，但是只有靠近地铁列车的那一端右手边的桥上才可以用路亚假鱼钓鱼。
地铁路线：乘坐MRT红线NS在Khatib 地铁站，出站后往左A出口直走，沿着地铁底部直走到看到一座天桥，上天桥过马路，再继续往同一个方向直走，会看到左边有3个很高白色尖角的三角形铁架建筑，绕道建筑的背面过马路就可以看到水库了，行程约15分钟。
地址：Vishun Ave 1 , Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
Singapore 769139
很适合带小孩来这个公园戏水,风景也很漂亮，这里可以跑步、踩单车、钓鱼,又靠近地铁站,是一个和家人或朋友聚会的好地方。

(Translated by Google)
The Lower Seletar Reservoir is a reservoir located east of Yishun New Town in the north of Singapore. The reservoir has a surface area of ​​3.6 square kilometers, a capacity of 9.5 million cubic meters, an average depth of 2 m and a maximum depth of 5.5 m. The length of the coastline is 14.3 kilometers.
The park is open 24 hours and admission is free.

Fishing friends who like fishing have two wooden bridges on the other side of the reservoir, but only the bridge on the right hand side near the end of the subway train can use lures to fish.
Subway route: Take the MRT Red Line NS at Khatib Subway Station, go straight to Exit A on the left after exiting the station, walk along the bottom of the subway until you see an overpass, cross the overpass on the overpass, and continue to go straight in the same direction, you will see To the left, there are 3 tall triangular iron-framed buildings with white sharp corners. Bypassing the back of the building and crossing the road, you can see the reservoir. The journey takes about 15 minutes.
Address: Vishun Ave 1, Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
Singapore 769139
It is very suitable to bring children to play in this park. The scenery is also very beautiful. You can run, cycle, and fish here. It is also close to the subway station. It is a good place to gather with family or friends.

name: Lower Seletar Reservoir Park
review_text:
这是个和orchid country  club 相连的公园，地方不大，但也能说五脏俱全，值得一说的是，这里能看到几种稀有飞禽，如白鹤。
这里因进行清洁工程，有几支机械船长期在湖上操作，而觅食的白鹤会停在铁平台上，等着吃被挖上的水草里的小鱼，情景难得，值得跑一趟看看，由其是小朋友们，会有一次难忘的记忆。
在这公园偶尔会有龙舟训练，我们也有机会看到独木舟小队，最难得的是每逢午后，几年来都会出现一对老鹰，它们是夫妻还是兄弟? 我看不懂它们之间的关系，但却能天天在相当固定的时间，望到它们在这片天宇飞舞，翱翔的姿态优雅得迷人，有时自己会忘我地欣赏它们大半个下午。
为了让岛国民众知道，这简小的角落多么有特色，我捕捉到今早的晨曦与大家分享。

(Translated by Google)
This is a park connected to the orchid country club. The place is not big, but it can also be said to have all the internal organs. It is worth mentioning that several rare birds can be seen here, such as white cranes.
Due to the cleaning project here, several mechanical boats have been operating on the lake for a long time, and the white cranes foraging will stop on the iron platform, waiting to eat the small fish in the dug up water plants. The scene is rare and worth a visit. , especially the children, there will be an unforgettable memory.
Occasionally there will be dragon boat training in this park, and we also have the opportunity to see the canoe team. The most rare thing is that every afternoon, a pair of eagles will appear for several years. Are they husband and wife or brothers? I can’t understand the relationship between them. But I can see them flying in this sky at a fairly fixed time every day, and their soaring posture is so graceful and charming. Sometimes I will enjoy them for most of the afternoon.
In order to let the people of the island country know how unique this small corner is, I captured the morning light this morning to share with you.
